description: You will love this crazy energetic book by a refreshing new talent! Tesana has never really fit into anything before but her daydreams. But when making an attempt to connect to her peers by joining in a pep rally planning committee she suddenly discovers a little white rabbit that lays brightly colored eggs. Realizing that she may have found the real life Easter bunny, Tesana embarks on an epic quest in an effort to get him back to his natural habitat and into safe hands. However as she progresses on her fanciful journey she gains more and more undesired attention until the quest becomes an increasingly madcap race to stay ahead of greedy pursuers and find a safe place for her new friend‚Ä¶wherever that place may be. It's Tesana against the world!

deck: Dolphin Book Edition 1986
description: Written by Harvey Pekar. Art by Kevin Brown, Gregory Budgett, R. Crumb, Gary Dumm, and Gerry Shamray. Cover by R. Crumb and Harvey Pekar. Introduction by R. Crumb. The best of AMERICAN SPLENDOR, the first literary comic book, is represented in this superbly illustrated collection by Harvey Pekar. The stories are both funny and touching, showing the delicate balance of personal relationships and the frustrations of the workday world. Pekar has been compared to Dreiser, Dostoevsky, and Lenny Bruce. That he is more himself than any of these will not be missed by readers of this omnibus.
name: American Splendor: The Life and Times of Harvey Pekar

deck: Volume 1.
description:
A New 52 on-going title starring John Constantine, launched after the cancellation of Constantine's long running Vertigo imprint title, Hellblazer, with issue #300.

During the publication of this volume, John was also appearing in Justice League Dark, and the two series often interacted with and affected each other.

The series was not exactly well received, with the main criticism being that it strayed too far from the tone of the original Hellblazer series, and became too involved with events from other DC titles (regularly interacting with Justice League Dark, and taking part in the Forever Evil: Blight, Trinity War, and Earth 2: World's End crossovers). In response, Constantine was cancelled, then retooled and relaunched as Constantine: The Hellblazer three months later.

Specials

  • Constantine: Futures End (#1)

Collected Editions

  • Vol. 1: The Spark and the Flame (#1-6)
  • Vol. 2: Blight (#7-12)
  • Vol. 3: The Voice In the Fire (#13-17)
  • Vol. 4: The Apocalypse Road (#18-23)

Issues of Constantine that tied into crossovers were also included in the following collections:

  • Justice League: Trinity War (#5)
  • Forever Evil: Blight (#9-12)
name: Constantine
